                                         JOHANNESBURG - The ANC has scheduled a special national executive committee meeting for Saturday morning as the party tries to deal with the multitude of court rulings and how they could affect the national conference.  Eyewitness News understands that Secretary-General Gwede Mantashe has called the meeting so that the party can decide on a way forward.  Earlier, the Pietermaritzburg High Court declared the KZN provincial leadership null and void, while the Bloemfontein High Court ordered that the outcome of the Free State ANCâ€™s elective conference is unlawful and void.